**Library Management System - Java Project**

## **Project Overview**
The goal of this project is to develop a **Library Management System** that allows users to borrow, return, and search for library items. The system will utilize **object-oriented programming concepts**, including inheritance, polymorphism, and abstract classes/interfaces. The project will also incorporate **exception handling, file I/O with CSV files, generics, recursion, and Java collections (List, Stack, Queue, Set, and Map)**.

## **Project Requirements**
### **Core Functionalities:**
1. **Users Management:**
   - Two types of users: `Student`, `Teacher`, and `Admin`.
   - Users have unique IDs, names, and a list of borrowed items.
   - Borrowing limits: Students can borrow up to **5 books (book only)**, while teachers can borrow up to **10 items** in total.

2. **Library Items Management:**
   - Three types of items: `Book`, `DVD`, and `Magazine`.
   - `Book` has attributes: `ISBN`, `title`, `author`, and `genre`.   (search for the ISBN valid pattern for the validation)
   - `DVD` has attributes: `title`, `director`, `duration (minutes)`.
   - `Magazine` has attributes: `title`, `issueNumber`, `publisher`.
   - Each item may have more than one copies, which means you may have 2 books with the same `ISBN`, `title`, `author` and `genre`, but with different `Id` to distinguish them.
   - Each item has a status to indicate if it is borrowed, in store or lost.

3. **Borrowing and Returning System:**
   - Users can borrow and return items.
   - Borrowing should check against user limits.
   - Implement **exception handling** for invalid operations (e.g., borrowing more than allowed, or all copies are borrowed).

4. **Searching and Reporting:**
   - Users can search for items by title or author (case-insensitive). If an item has more than one copy, the search result should only contain one copy of them
   - Implement a **recursive** version search method for finding items.
   - Implement also a **stream** version search method for finding items.
   - Admin can generate a report of all borrowed/in-store/lost items (implements an `Reportable` interface).

5. **Data Persistence:**
   - Load **CSV fiels** to initialize items and users
   - Admin can call the method to backup current users and items into two **CSV files**.

6. **Sorting:**
   - Provide different sorting strategies for User and Item

